title: By the Queene. The Queenes Maiesties proclamation, declaring her princely intention to inhibite her subiects vpon most extreme paynes from offending on the seas any persons in their ships or goods, being the subiected of any prince, potentate or state, in amitie with her Maiestie.
author: England and Wales. Sovereign (1558-1603 : Elizabeth I)
publisher: By the deputies of Christopher Barker, printer to the Queenes most excellent Maiestie,
